HEADWORD: off-putting
<hw>off-putting</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>hard to deal
with.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> awkward, disconcerting, embarrassing, sticky, tight,
unenviable.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>tending to repel.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> unappealing.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><q>The trappings of upper-class life are <qex>off-putting</qex> and
sterile.</q> <rj><qau>Elizabeth Hess</qau></rj></p>

